---
description: When you have Figma: translate intent to tokens, not pixels
alwaysApply: true
---

## If Figma is provided
- Ask for: frame link, target breakpoint(s), and any token source (Tailwind config/CSS vars).
- Match **layout + hierarchy + spacing rhythm** first, not exact pixel positions.
- Reuse existing components if present (buttons, inputs, cards).
- Prefer Tailwind theme tokens; avoid hardcoded hex unless no token exists.

## If no Figma (invent design)
- Propose 2 concise variants (e.g. “clean neutral”, “accented”) and implement the best fit.
- Keep UI consistent: same radii, same shadows, same spacing scale across the feature.
